Eating healthily doesn’t have to be expensive, in fact you will probably save
money. It’s possible to make good quality, healthy meals without breaking the
The best way to cut your food costs is to plan your meals, using our meal
planner, make a shopping list (and stick to it) and cook from scratch at home.
There are many ways you can eat a healthy, balanced diet on a budget. Buying
tinned or frozen fruit and veg, creating dishes with leftovers and whipping up
a healthy meal from what you have in your store cupboard will help you save
Check out some tips for cooking on a budget.
If you're stuck for ideas of what to cook, check out the recipes in our recipe
